Same goes for a type 3 engine which I have on my dune buggy. But is should
be noted that you can only keep driving AS LONG AS YOUR BATTERY WILL HOLD
OUT. So if this does happen it's a good idea to stop cranking the stereo,
turn off lights and fans, etc.

